        "content": "<p>What I expect will be helpful is even more precise mathematical definitions. For example here I wasn't immediately sure if \"with elements\" meant \"generated by\". Also, isn't <code>α^(-3)</code> equal to <code>-1</code>? In gaugeGroupℤ₃SubGroup I believe there are 2 choices you can make. Do you care which one?</p>",
        "id": 471312928,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1726680688
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"111080\">@Floris van Doorn</span> thanks for this, and thanks for your comment and for taking a look :). </p>\n<p>By \"with elements\" I really meant that the subgroup <code>ℤ₆</code> of <code>GaugeGroupIˣ</code> consisting of the six elements of the form <code>(α ^ 2 • 1, α ^ (-3 : ℤ) • 1, α)</code> where <code>α</code> is a sixth root of unity. But I understand that this wasn't clear, and I thank you for pointing this out. </p>\n<p>I believe the definition you have is (trivially) equivalent to what I wanted however.</p>",
        "id": 471315770,
        "sender_full_name": "Joseph Tooby-Smith",
        "timestamp": 1726681699
    },
